               <p>
                        <persName>Dorothy ('Dolly'</persName>) was the sister of <persName>
                            <ptr target="/persons/pers0763.xml"/>Samuel Furly (or Furley</persName>), and
                  joined him as a correspondent of <persName>
                            <ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>. On <date when="1764-06-26">June 26, 1764</date> she married
                        <persName>
                            <ptr target="/persons/pers0610.xml"/>John Downes</persName> in
                     <placeName>Bristol</placeName>. <persName>Dorothy</persName> survived her
                  husband by three decades, being buried in <placeName>Leeds</placeName> on <date when="1807-08-01">Aug. 1, 1807</date>.</p>
            
         
